===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
One of the three characters ([[無]], [[无]], [[亡]]) that has historically been used to represent the word "no, not any". First attested in {{w|Warring States period}}, used interchangable with 無 until {{w|Tang Dynasty}}. Readopted by {{w|People's Republic of China|PRC}} in 1956.

The origin of this character is unknown. Probably an acient variant form of either [[元]], [[天]] or [[尧]].

